---
import ServiceLayout from '@/layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import Container from '@/components/ui/Container.astro';
import SchemaFAQ from '@/components/seo/SchemaFAQ.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Custom Cabinetry"
  metaTitle="Custom Cabinetry Seattle WA | Handcrafted Kitchen & Bath Cabinets | Best KB Remodeling"
  metaDescription="Handcrafted custom cabinetry for Seattle kitchens and bathrooms. Built to your exact specifications with premium hardwoods and finishes. Expert design and installation. Free estimates!"
  slug="custom-cabinetry"
  category="kitchen"
  heroImage="/images/service-custom-cabinetry.jpg"
  features={[
    'Fully custom dimensions to fit any space',
    'Premium hardwood construction (maple, cherry, walnut, white oak)',
    'Dovetail joinery and plywood box construction',
    'Soft-close hinges and full-extension drawer glides',
    'Custom interior organizers and specialty inserts',
    'Hand-applied finish options (stain, paint, lacquer)',
    'Matching crown molding, trim, and accessories',
  ]}
>
  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
    <p class="text-xl text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
      Custom cabinetry represents the pinnacle of kitchen and bathroom craftsmanship. Unlike stock or semi-custom options, fully custom cabinets are built from scratch to your exact measurements, style preferences, and functional requirements. Every door profile, every interior configuration, and every finish detail is chosen by you and executed by skilled woodworkers. The result is cabinetry that fits your space perfectly and reflects your personal taste down to the smallest detail.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      What Makes Custom Cabinets Different
    </h2>
    <p>
      Stock cabinets come in fixed sizes, typically in 3" width increments. Semi-custom cabinets offer some size modifications and finish choices. Custom cabinets, by contrast, are manufactured to the exact dimensions your space requires — down to 1/16 of an inch. This means no filler strips hiding gaps, no wasted space in corners, and no compromises on depth, height, or width.
    </p>
    <p>
      Construction quality is equally distinctive. Our custom cabinets feature 3/4" furniture-grade plywood box construction rather than particleboard, dovetail drawer joinery rather than staples, solid wood face frames rather than veneered MDF, and hand-applied finishes that are sanded between coats for a glass-smooth result. These construction details ensure your cabinets look beautiful and perform flawlessly for 30+ years.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Wood Species and Finish Options
    </h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Maple:</strong> Our most popular species, maple offers a fine, uniform grain that takes stain evenly and provides a smooth surface for painted finishes. Its hardness (rated 1,450 on the Janka scale) makes it extremely durable in high-traffic kitchens.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Cherry:</strong> Beloved for its rich, warm tones that deepen over time with exposure to light. Cherry's straight grain and smooth texture create elegant traditional and transitional cabinets. We offer cherry in natural, light stain, and deep espresso finishes.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>White Oak:</strong> Increasingly popular for its distinctive grain pattern and natural durability. White oak's open pores create a beautiful texture when wire-brushed, and it pairs perfectly with the organic, nature-inspired design trends popular in Seattle homes. Quarter-sawn white oak adds dramatic ray fleck patterns for an Arts and Crafts aesthetic.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Walnut:</strong> The most luxurious domestic hardwood, walnut features rich chocolate-brown tones with striking grain variations. Custom walnut cabinets make a bold design statement and are particularly stunning with a natural oil finish that highlights the wood's depth and warmth.
    </p>
    <p>
      Paint-grade options include premium maple and MDF for clients who want a flawless painted finish. We offer factory-sprayed catalyzed lacquer finishes in any color, providing a durable, professional-quality result that resists chipping and yellowing.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Interior Customization
    </h2>
    <p>
      The inside of a custom cabinet is just as thoughtfully designed as the outside. We integrate pull-out trash and recycling bins, spice drawer inserts, knife block dividers, peg board dish storage systems, pull-out pantry shelves, corner cabinet turntables and pull-outs, tray dividers, under-sink organizers, and mixer lift platforms. Every inch of interior space is planned for maximum utility based on how you actually cook and live.
    </p>
    <p>
      We also design specialty cabinets that stock manufacturers simply don't offer: appliance garages with retractable tambour doors, built-in dog feeding stations, wine storage with proper bottle cradles and glass racks, integrated charging drawers with built-in outlets, and toe-kick drawers that add hidden storage in the typically wasted space at floor level.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Our Custom Cabinetry Partners
    </h2>
    <p>
      We work with several Pacific Northwest cabinet shops that share our commitment to quality craftsmanship. These small, local manufacturers allow us to oversee production closely, ensure materials meet our standards, and maintain shorter lead times than national custom cabinet brands. Every cabinet is built in the greater Seattle area, supporting local skilled trades and reducing transportation-related damage risks.
    </p>
    <p>
      From your first design consultation through final installation, our team manages the entire process. We handle design, engineering, ordering, delivery coordination, and installation with our own trained crews — never subcontracted labor. The result is a seamless experience and a finished product that exceeds your expectations.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <Fragment slot="faq">
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
      <Container>
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mb-10 text-center">
            Custom Cabinetry FAQs
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                How much do custom cabinets cost compared to stock?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Custom cabinets typically cost $500-$1,200 per linear foot installed, compared to $100-$300 for stock and $200-$600 for semi-custom. For a typical Seattle kitchen with 25-30 linear feet of cabinetry, custom cabinets range from $15,000-$35,000. While the upfront cost is higher, custom cabinets offer superior construction, perfect fit, unlimited design options, and a lifespan of 30+ years compared to 10-15 years for most stock options.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                How long does it take to get custom cabinets?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                From final design approval to delivery, custom cabinets typically take 6-10 weeks to manufacture. We work with local Pacific Northwest shops, so lead times are shorter than national custom brands that may take 12-16 weeks. Installation takes 2-4 days depending on the kitchen's size. We recommend beginning the design process 3-4 months before your desired installation date.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                Do I need custom cabinets or will semi-custom work?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Semi-custom cabinets work well for most standard kitchens with conventional layouts. Custom is the better choice when you have non-standard ceiling heights, unusual angles or alcoves, very specific style preferences, or when you want specialty interior configurations. During your consultation, we'll show you both options and help you determine which offers the best value for your specific project.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                Can you build custom cabinets for bathrooms too?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Yes, we build custom vanities, linen cabinets, and storage towers for bathrooms. Custom bathroom cabinetry is especially valuable when dealing with non-standard plumbing locations, tight spaces, or when you want a unique furniture-style vanity that can't be found in retail options. All bathroom cabinetry uses moisture-resistant construction methods appropriate for the humid environment.
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Container>
    </section>
  </Fragment>

  <SchemaFAQ items={[
    { question: 'How much do custom cabinets cost compared to stock?', answer: 'Custom cabinets typically cost $500-$1,200 per linear foot installed, compared to $100-$300 for stock and $200-$600 for semi-custom. For a typical Seattle kitchen with 25-30 linear feet of cabinetry, custom cabinets range from $15,000-$35,000. While the upfront cost is higher, custom cabinets offer superior construction, perfect fit, unlimited design options, and a lifespan of 30+ years compared to 10-15 years for most stock options.' },
    { question: 'How long does it take to get custom cabinets?', answer: 'From final design approval to delivery, custom cabinets typically take 6-10 weeks to manufacture. We work with local Pacific Northwest shops, so lead times are shorter than national custom brands that may take 12-16 weeks. Installation takes 2-4 days depending on the kitchen\'s size. We recommend beginning the design process 3-4 months before your desired installation date.' },
    { question: 'Do I need custom cabinets or will semi-custom work?', answer: 'Semi-custom cabinets work well for most standard kitchens with conventional layouts. Custom is the better choice when you have non-standard ceiling heights, unusual angles or alcoves, very specific style preferences, or when you want specialty interior configurations. During your consultation, we\'ll show you both options and help you determine which offers the best value for your specific project.' },
    { question: 'Can you build custom cabinets for bathrooms too?', answer: 'Yes, we build custom vanities, linen cabinets, and storage towers for bathrooms. Custom bathroom cabinetry is especially valuable when dealing with non-standard plumbing locations, tight spaces, or when you want a unique furniture-style vanity that can\'t be found in retail options. All bathroom cabinetry uses moisture-resistant construction methods appropriate for the humid environment.' },
  ]} />
</ServiceLayout>
